        <abstract>
            <p>Galton agrees with GJR about rudimentary organs.</p>
            <p>GJR’s note referred to possibility of selection acting on organic types as distinguished from individuals.</p> 
<p>Thinks Grant Allen has not made out his point [in <hi rend="italic">Physiological aesthetics</hi> (1877)], but his fundamental principle probably has much truth.</p> 
        </abstract>
